Title:
Hybrid of subspace and its complement - with custom operators

Solves with hamiltonian

P H0 P + (1-P) H1 (1-P) + Hint[t]

P........ projector onto a subspace
H0....... Hamiltonian on subspace
H1....... Hamiltonian on orthogonal complement of suspace
Hint[t]...time-dependent operator connecting all

The subspace is composed of eigenfunctions of some operator (in this case: H0)
expressed in the basis (see Axis:... entries below)

# NOTE: this should produce identical results to a system w/o the separation
#       the model is Harm Muller's Argon

#define BOX    20.
#define SMOOTH 15.

#define mullerA 5.4
#define mullerB 1
#define mullerC 3.682
#define mullerR 3
#define mullerF 2.5
#define mullerG 2.01785

#define MullerV (1+mullerA*exp(-mullerB*Q)+(17-mullerA)*exp(-mullerC*Q))/Q
#define MullerW chi[0,mullerR]*mullerF*(pow[5]((mullerR-Q)/mullerG)-pow[4]((mullerR-Q)/mullerG))

#define MullerArgon (1/2<<Laplacian>>+<1><1><-MullerV+MullerW>)

Surface: points
20.

# Explanation of the Subspace entry:
# - Compute Eigenbasis of MullerArgon in the discretization of Complement
# - select 1 eigenvector starting from eigenvector 4 (1-dimensional subspace)

Axis: subset,name,nCoefficients,lower end, upper end,functions,order
Subspace,Orbital,1,4,,Eigenbasis[MullerArgon:Complement]
Complement,Phi, 1,,,expIm
          ,Eta,4,-1,1, assocLegendre{Phi}
          ,Rn,40, 0.,mullerR,polynomial,20
          ,Rn,BOX*2, mullerR,BOX,polynomial,20
          ,Rn,20, BOX,Infty,polExp[0.5]



Absorption: kind, axis, theta, upper
ECS,Rn,0.3,BOX

Operator: hamiltonian=<0,0>MullerArgon+<1,1>MullerArgon

# NOTE: above Subspace and Complement both use H0=H1=MullerArgon
# Alternative example: Hydrogen atom
# Operator: hamiltonian=<0,0>MullerArgon+<1,1>(0.5<<Laplacian>>-<<Coulomb>>)

Operator: interaction=<allOnes>(iLaserAx[t]<<D/DX>>+iLaserAy[t]<<D/DY>>+iLaserAz[t]<<D/DZ>>)

Laser: shape, I(W/cm2), FWHM, lambda(nm), phiCEO
cos2, 1.e10, 4 OptCyc, 800.,   0.
cos4, 1.e11, 3 OptCyc, 800./13,0.
cos4, 1.e11, 3 OptCyc, 800./15,0.

Initial: kind=Orbital[0]

TimePropagation: end,print,store,cutEnergy,accuracy
  20 OptCyc, 0.5 OptCyc,0.05 au,20,1.e-9

Spectrum: radialPoints=100


